title: Independent candidate Razi Ullah Khan wins PP-226 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 09 (APP): Independent Candidate, Razi Ullah Khan has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-226 Lodharan-II by securing 65,434 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Shah Muhammad of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) who bagged 60,133 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 51.95%.
